==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lambert pine
<hw>Lam"bert pine`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from
<etsep>Lambert</etsep>, an English botanist.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The gigantic sugar pine of California and Oregon (<spn>Pinus
Lambertiana</spn>). It has the leaves in fives, and cones a foot long.
The timber is soft, and like that of the white pine of the Eastern
States.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lambis</ent>⟦br⟧
